= render 'shared/about_modal', id: 'yearlyElectricRatesAboutModal', title: 'About Yearly Electric Rates Data' do
  .d-flex.mb-4
    = render 'shared/modal/about_this_calculation' do
      %p.mb-3
        %strong When multiple reporting entities serve a single area in a given year
        (such as Anchorage), we calculate a 
        %span.text-primary.fw-bold sales-weighted average
        to provide a more accurate representation of the cost for most residents.
    
      %p.mb-3
        Instead of a simple midpoint, this approach weights each utility's rate by their actual sales volume (MWh). This ensures that a utility serving ~&nbsp80% of residents has an ~&nbsp80% impact on the trend line.
    
      .bg-light.p-3.border.rounded.small.mb-0
        %span.text-dark.fw-bold For Example (2017 Anchorage Residential Rates):
        %ul.list-unstyled.mb-0.mt-2
          %li 
            Chugach Electric (505,275 MWh sold): 
            %strong $0.20
          %li 
            Municipal Light & Power (127,375 MWh sold): 
            %strong $0.21
          %li.mt-2.pt-2.border-top
            %strong The Weighted Math:
            .mt-1.text-muted
              ((0.20 × 505,275) + (0.21 × 127,375)) / 632,650 Total MWh =
            .mt-1
              /%strong Result: 
              %span.text-success.fw-bold $0.202 per kWh
            %p.mt-1.mb-0.extra-small.text-muted
              * A simple average would have been $0.205.